<br>
If you are, sign up on the link below, and show up on time. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everquestraids.com/Events/EventDetails.asp?EID=3468">www.everquestraids.com/Ev...p?EID=3468</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Rules for the raid and rules for the loot are posted on the messages following it.  This is for the three allied guilds, no one else at this point.  We're going to try to clear the plane and get as many named mobs as we have the power to do.  Because of this second goal we need to start early, as in 11AM EST.  First, to get <br>
there before any other guilds arrive, and second to make sure we still have the needed people for the big <br>
game at the end.<br>
<br>
The big game at the end is what separates PoG and makes it great loot.  The named mobs ALWAYS drop a piece of armor, some of them ALWAYS drop a breastplate or robe.  Please sign up so I know we have enough and am not forced to invite others from other guilds.  Would like this to be alliance only if possible.<br>
<br>
Any questions, send them here or better yet post them on the Everquestraids board and I'll answer them as I can.  Let's go have some fun!<br>
<br>
Last time we went we had 13 armor drops for classes, 4 other great rare items, 17 rare gems, and 31 spells.  No waiting for silly gems, just pick it up, put it on, and sport it in front of all your friends.<br>
<br>
Hope to see you all there!<br>
<br>
PS - For those with faction issues.  PoG killing effects three things and three things only:<br>
<br>
The inhabitants of Growth themselves<br>
One guild in Kelethin<br>
One guild in Felwithe<br>
<br>
You may still wander happily through either of these two cities, you just have to know which guild in each city to avoid.<br>
